PROJECTS

MBurst GPS Board Payload

Determined how various GPS sensors performed on weather balloons at high altitude conditions. Worked on a payload with an array of 4 different GPS: Adafruit Ultimate GPS, Titan X1, Pam-7Q, Cam-M8

Machine Learning

Used binary trees and sorting algorithms to recognize certain inputs and classify post on Piazza in C++ for EECS 280: Programming and Introductory Data Structures. Posts were classified based on keywords and the frequency of use of those key words.

Maize nâ€™ Balloon Weather Balloon Launch

Collaborated with four other team members to create a payload designed to collect data during a weather balloon flight. Designed and tested a printed circuit board and foam payload container. Programmed eight different components to work in unity to record and transmit data throughout the flight. Those components include, a humidity sensor, accelerometer, pressure sensor, TMP36, thermistor, Xbee, OpenLog, and GPS.

Alpha Blog

Created a website hosted on Heroku using Ruby on Rails that allows you to create, edit, delete and show various articles. This project was done for a Udemy Course.

HATACHE: #BuiltByGirls Challenge Project

Designed a hat that helps to relieve the pain caused by headaches and migraines for the #BuiltByGirls Challenge. Developed a prototype that contained an electronic heating and cooling system in the form of a Peltier Plate and a rechargeable power source comprised of lithium batteries and a circuit board. Fabric infused with lavender.

Message Me

Created a messaging website using Ruby on Rails. The site has login capabilities and allows users to messages their friends. This project was done for a Udemy Course.

Finance tracker

Created a website that allows you to track your finances, stocks, and follow your friends' finances using Ruby on Rails. This project was done for a Udemy Course.

ABOUT

My name is Lauren Stanciel. I am a sophomore majoring in Computer Science with a minor in Space and Climate Engineering at the University of Michigan in the College of Engineering. I am proficient in C++, C and Java. I was chosen by Google Developers to be the first ever Developer Student Club Lead at my university. I am the External Relations Co-Chair for Student Space Systems Fabrication Lab. As well as being a member of the Management Leadership for Tomorrow 2022 Software Engineering Career Prep class. I am really passionate about using technology to help us learn and connect to the world around us.
